---

<section>
    <div class="description">
        <p>
            Master the types and wiring methods of digital inputs, and learn to
            access common digital sensors.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="learning-points">
        <h2>ðŸ“š Learning Points</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Switching Signals: Introduce the characteristics of passive
                switching (dry contact) and active switching (wet contact)
            </li>
            <li>
                Switching Sensor Wiring: Using water level sensors (float
                switches) and limit switches as examples to demonstrate
                passive/active wiring
            </li>
            <li>
                NPN (Open Collector) Signal: Introduce the wiring method of NPN
                output sensors (such as photoelectric switches)
            </li>
            <li>
                Pulse/Frequency Input: Explain how to access flowmeters with
                pulse output or frequency signals for counting or frequency
                detection
            </li>
            <li>
                IIC Digital Communication Interface: Demonstrate the hardware
                access of the IIC interface (SCL/SDA/GND/3V) and accessing IIC
                temperature and humidity sensors (such as SHT30)
            </li>
            <li>
                Input Parameter Status View: View switching status, frequency
                values, temperature/humidity, and other data in the app
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>
